oh yeah. plus this... just because :)

How do I love thee? Let me count the ways.
I love thee to the depth and breadth and height
My soul can reach, when feeling out of sight
for the ends of Being and Ideal Grace.
I love thee to the level of every day's
Most quiet need, by sun and candlelight.
I love thee freely, as men strive for Right:
I love thee purely, as they turn from Praise:
I love thee with the passion put to use
In my old griefs, and with my childhood's faith;
I love thee with a love I seemed to lose
With my lost saints, - I love thee with the breath,
Smiles, tears, of all my life! - and, if God choose,
I shall but love thee better after death. 


                   Elizabeth Barrett Browning

Its really all about why, and then how falls into place.
WHY is all that matters

<3Arly-Lian

<lj-cut text="Behold Happiness in a Japanese Kid Snack">http://www.japanesesnacks.com/JSLinkout/o.php?out=http://www.asiafoods.com</lj-cut> Does any one else remeber these? I feel like I'm going crazy.. maybe no one had them in Maryland. Anyway, I was shopping w/ Allison this weekend and found these <333 thats the japanese version-- they like made some for america.

yeah, nightschool. they cancelled my software app class because of low enrollment - which is crap because there were 3 seniors in that class that needed it to graduate- I feel so bad for them. Its not offered anywhere else either. Ugh its so unfair. such crap.

and then in health- this guy that sits next to me gave this other guy a cigarrette... and they just talk about all of the drugs and things they do. It just makes me sad.. people just throw their lives away... and don't care. Whats worse is, that some of them are a lot more decent that most of the fake "good kids" ugh. self destruction. also crap. 

and then when I say something people think that I'm being self righteous.. like I think I'm better than them. But in reality, I know in a lot of ways they're better than me and it drives me crazy that all of these doors are closing on them and the rest of the world turns they're back on them just because their flaws/vices/problems are more immediate or evident than mine. I just wish they could see what they were doing to themselves... like they're good people, they dont deserve it.

okay, I really shouldn't have updated, I have to go do all of this homework it all seems so stupid when you can do things like <lj-cut text="this"> http://crossculturalsolutions.org/</lj-cut> thats life. thats real. now is just busy work until it all matters.

i hate waiting. 

                                                                        but i love loving you
<3Arly-Lian

So I just got back from the Model Un conference this weekend. It was fabulous. But it was mostly fabulous when I wasn't actually at the conference. It was exceptionally fabulous when I was suposed to be there and wasn't. ;) <3

wahoo for Costa Rica and diplomacy.
The conference was at the Washington Hilton which is right in Dupont Circle aka. gay people central. It was fabulous walking around though because I wasn't worried about being mugged. :) AND I found this beautiful second hand book store..teehee.<3333
 
as well as Secondi's, which is like this consignment store for like funky vintage designer stuff (many thanks to Allison). 

Blech.. today was so lovely, and now I'm back to life. As soon as I got home I had to run to piano, and now I'm off to nightschool. Oh well these dreary moments will be later compensated by lovely ones with amazing people, so I can't be discouraged.

DC is beautiful. Its so full of life and wonderfulness and I'm glad I carry lovely memories of it. :)

*sigh* yay.

<3Arly-Lian

Haha. I'm in nightschool rightnow... there are like 4 other people in my class... and they are watching American Idol. I should be reading Frankenstein, but I found this amusing. Hope your lives are a little more interesting.

HAPPY BIRTHDAY CARMEN!

(dang.. I wish I could make that scroll across)

Ugh. There is no way I could write a proper entry that would do Carmen justice.

Just know that if you live in MD, be sad because you don't know her.

If you live in Miami, be sad that you haven't met her.

 She's amazing. Our friendship is one of the best things that could've ever happened to me. I don't know where I'd be without her. Just know that if you ever have a friend even close to the kind of person she is, you're a lucky kid.

luf you!
school. blah/wahoo? I don't know... you get what you get...so you might as well be outrageously joyful. I saw some lovely people though, so all in all twas a good day.

Day 1005789
I feel like a mother.

I've cracked... out comes apathy.
Give me a call when you care.


*cross my heart and kiss my elbow*



                                                                       Merelyn

I've been playing the piano so much lately I feel like my fingers are going to bleed.
 
It just feels so good to get lost in the music. I'm not particular to a genre or anything because each one feels like a piece of myself. I wish I could just play things, my musical ineptness hinders my ability to interpret the songs.

I hate it when the world is right... you feel like everyone is saying I told you so.

I actually have my piano recital today. This lady is like my 8th piano teacher.
Like my mother always wanted to me to play the piano and she would always tell me to never stop because I would regret it. and of course I did and now of course I'm back playing rinkydink pieces from a lesson book with animated eighth notes on the cover. 

Its not just the piano...it kind of just everything. 

Jack of all trades- master of none. Arni-Elei warned me of that when I started getting into so much stuff. Once again... they told me so.

I feel like I never deal with anything... I kind of sugar coat it and leave it alone to avoid a scene. It drives me crazy when my mom is loud in a store... I just feel like melting and hoping no one sees me I'm so scared of making a scene. 

I kind of want my fingers to bleed.. at least it will be real... maybe I'll make a scene.

I forsee this year as an atypical one.

<3Arly-Lian

wow. I need to update but really should not be. this week has been a millennium and *whoosh* at the same time. okay... quick recap. while I multi-task talking to Kat and Mogus.

MONDAY-Forensics, debate, HOMEWORK!!! like crazy. *wooshed* back into school.
TUESDAY-more debate... getting ready for the meet. studying... homework...etc. i think it was tuesday... or maybe thursday but professor (jane says it like that... i think its cool) hobson is all like " our country should legalize marijuana and tax it like crazy. getting high is just the same as getting drunk." what. the. ....crap. *fumes* i'll save the hobson rant for a later time. 
WEDNESDAY- Debate meet! woot. I was soo nervous. It was worth it because I won both. *throws about confetti* wow, but it was cool...considering I put it off FOREVER! gosh... my debate team must think i'm soo irresponsible. I was there like forever though. Speaking of irresponsible.. i had an implementation meeting that night (and missed it...gosh this is the 3rd one)  and mutual... which i also missed. I always miss that. I'm making a commitment not to anymore though... i must prioritize. *determination*
THURSDAY- Executive board meeting. I felt soo bad. Eric had called me the other night to get something together before then and I never called him back.We always get get by by deciding stuff before the meeting anyways. wow..i have to got rid of that bad habit too. gah. *PUBLICITY ATTEMPT* For anyone who wants to go its Jan.29 at Carver 7-8:30 *ding* that is all. (well not really)
FRIDAY- Fashion show in English... I dressed up as Bobo the Hobo which is apparently this kids screenname. Anywho. It was pretty "derelict" (hehe...for all of you who have seen zoolander) I wore a target bag for a tank top and a water bottle mini skirt. Some people were cool with it and others were well... typical. Its all good though... it reminded me of Miami. (actually everyone should start wearing bags now.. that would be so awesome!)We rehearsed for forensics till i had to leave to go babysit. Then.. i babysat. yup. came home. slept. you know the deal.
SATURDAY- FORENSICS MEET! I overslept and showed up late... but I made it. I did extemp and prose. Wow... I was busy. I ran over all four rounds though on prose and finished early on all of my extemporaneous. Oo! We also did reader's theater and went up after this mad talented group.. they were so funny. we went and looked horrible though. Its okay i guess.. all the girls I did it with are awesome. (and i was ariel !!!!) Drama is awesome. woopwoop... i just realized i'm like a drama wannabe. *pitiful* eh. Its okay though... a learning experience as my mom likes to call it. I got home at like 5 and didn't wake up untill ten the next morning. IT WAS JESSICA'S BIRTHDAY AND I DIDN'T CALL HER! I WANT TO DIE. I FEEL SO BAD. I AM A CRAPPY MCCRAPPERSON FRIEND. WOW. SHOOT ME.
SUNDAY- I woke up and went to the joint stake thinger mehoo (only after my mom rode halfway to the MV chapel and realized it). I was all pumped up.. oh yeah. go mormons.:) and then had a presidency meeting at Sis. Palmers. She's so cute or should i say...SUPERCUTE! My presidency is too. <3 to them .BTW other announcement: Mia Maid sleepover 26-27... myhouse! *ding*

 wow... if you're still reading this you really love me (so much for a quick recap) so please...continue.

today. school was... tiring.  i got the psat scores back and did pretty crummy. i missed the ezine meeting and putting on the hits dress rehearsal *feels bad* because of my stupid doctors appointment at 3:30. I hate the doctors office. She said nothing freaking new and my mom has to pay a billion dollars. Plus she's (my mom) is still convinced that i have anemia and wants the doctor to say it. So i go there to the doctor and she's like "i'm pretty sure  you don't have anemia. *sigh of relief (now my mom doesn't have that 'its because you're vegetarian excuse')* but...i'll send you to get blood drawn." *dies* YOU JUST SAID I"M NOT ANEMIC  BUT YOU ARE GOING TO SUCK BLOOD OUT OF MY BODY WITH A POINTY METAL APPARATUS??? gah. so know i'm just procrastinating. writing to whoever is still reading this. 

OMG! Arni-Elei got the Michael Jackson Number Ones dvd. wow. He is like the master. the king. MICHAEL ROCKS!!! holy crap. soo cool. <3 to Mickey J (alayna.. when you come up we will have to commit certain sections to memory)like i knew he was awesome before but like now? whoa. whole new obsession. 

SOMEONE ELSE WHO IS ALSO INCREDIBLE (and i am thinking of at the moment...): 
MS JASPER IS SOOO AWESOME. She calls my house tonight and says I don't have to bother with the bibliography speech because it wouldn't change my a anyway. This woman's dad dies new years eve and she's making phone calls to my house for my benefit and for all of her students. Like... I <3 HER! She is sooo awesome. O M G. I *loss for words.* 

ack... Pippin auditions tomorrow. *dies*

anywho... i hope you enjoyed this entry because i probably won't have a life for like another week. so i luf you all.

farewell.

<3Arly-Lian

hmm. today i went to the gym again. omg it felt sooo good. like sooooooo good. ohman. but its like the first time in 2 months. i'm so out of shape now. even moreso. bah. i want to go back so bad. its such a release. the pain is like...addictive. plus arlon-glenn's wedding is in like 2 months so i better get crackin. allison asked me to be her bridesmaid.(i know its so sweet) why do i tell you this? i entreat you for help. the next time you see that sourpatch kid inch toward my mouth... take it away. hopefully with a preceeding self-esteem shattering comment. ie. better luck next time fattie. shut your black hole of compulsive eating you..fathead. be creative! anywho. you get my drift.

other than my workout, today amounted to nothing as well. great way to ring in the new year. i don't know... years just seem to come and go now, its weird.

now all i've got to finish are these debate constructives, stupid math scrapbook, write my ezine article, do mcr stuff and probably something else important i can't remember. argh. i can only blame myself. anywho, i luf you all.

<3 Arly-Lian

new years eve was weird. i was reluctantly getting ready to go to the dance. i'm not a fan of the-- well thats a whole other entry. anyways, i'm getting ready and all i need is some eyeliner. i start looking and can't find it when all of a sudden i start to cry. like. crazy. and i don't know why and i keep crying and crying and i was just like i can't go to the dance.. i don't have eyeliner. i was like the cosmetic straw that broke the camel's back. so i basically rang in the new year with regret, in sweatpants and drinking apple juice (no sparkling cider) no matter.. oh wait.. yes matter. today amounted to nothing as well. except a whole lot of people have ljs now. woohoo! muahahaha! 
i just don't know.. i'm caught in this whirlpool of nothingness... maybe because there's nothing for me to worry about and i just enjoy self pity. what do you all care anyways? i guess you must care something if you're reading this. well i <3 you all despite the roller coaster this entry has been. 

its almost tomorrow. (wow kind of deep) i better post this. 

<3Arly-Lian

the call log:
sunday night/monday morning? thanks to aditi i only talked on the phone till 2:30 giving me about 7 hours of sleep.
monday night/tuesday morning? i believe i challenged the standing record talking on the phone with austin...again. i got to sleep around 5:30.
that and the previous evenings give me a grand total of 15-16 hours since friday. 
*dies*
but these lovely chats were not in vain. i learned a lovely array of facts including if austin were a crayon he would be burnt sienna and that einstein married his cousin and that conniption fit is spelled that way and that he ..had a rabbit named pj and that we both like mint chocolate chip ice cream, fall/summer and those two windy weeks, neatness and miss home etc.... i was fun... these are clearly important things to know :)

anywho 
monday-monday was return day aka. brutal honesty and take the guilt trip afterwards day. i slept in... which i hate doing because my day gets cut in half. yet still managed to go to best buy and go crazy.  thanks to my bluntness i returned a bunch of stuff and od on cds. theres nothing like screamo...oh yeah. then i chilled at austins with aditi and mostly talked to his mom. its okay though shes a cutie. and later continued the austin marathon w/ a hint of aditi

tuesday-my mom woke me up at like 9:45 after like 4 hours of sleep mind you and informed me that i would be babysitting in an hour.  nothing like 3 2-7 year old tackling you for piggy back rides to wake you up. we popped in finding nemo and had a grand old time. seriously though, those kids are cute. then i flew off to a forensics meeting. i wish i knew the drama people better. alot of them seem pretty cool and sooo talented. *bows down* the meet is the 10th and i still don't know what i'm doing... gah. well i have until the 10th to procrastinate that one. arni-elei's friend tony is here.. staying for a day.. hes cool. man i remember when i used to throw stuff at his brother. good times.

now i want to do something and nobody's here. bah. if anyone wants to do anything this week OMG please call the cell. maybe my life will be interesting enough that i'll actually not have time to update every 2 seconds. wow. that was desperate. you should feel sorry for me. i feel sorry for me. oh well. i luf you all.

<3 Arly-Lian

my <3 bleeds for you...
 i've been thinking about alot of people lately. people that will probably never read this as well as people who may read this religiously and never comment. alot of people that don't even no me or associate my name with a distant memory. its probably alot better than the person i am now. hold on to that memory. know that i love you and think about you. i won't forget you. 

<3 Arly-Lian

hurray...my first livejournal..whilst some of you may be proud others may want to kill me. for the latter...all you have to do is not read it. i figured i should get one f these considered i never talk to anyone anyways...at least you'll know how i'm doing. i'm not too sure how long this is going to last though..i never keep up at anything for too long. now that i've finally got this...i'm off to procrastinate doing the homework i procrastinated to do this. toodles.

hehe this is pretty funny..considering that no one knows i have one of these the first entry i write is to meself. hehe.

btw- if anyone wants to be added to the friends list.. wherein which i have ever so many people.. let me know.
